15:29.414 --> 15:29.460
So, your summer at Wyler,
did you a offer, or...?

15:29.460 --> 15:32.486
No. They had a hiring freeze.
The economy.

15:32.530 --> 15:35.249
But I would rather
be here, anyway.
Just an odd question,

15:35.300 --> 15:38.189
it's a question they asked me
when I first interviewed here.

15:38.230 --> 15:39.595
What's your favorite hobby?

15:39.630 --> 15:41.530
Well, I'm embarrassed
to say it.

15:41.570 --> 15:44.300
(laughs):
Oh, come on, Martha,
let's hear it.

15:44.340 --> 15:45.659
What was your hobby?
No, no,

15:45.710 --> 15:48.201
no, no-- I'm the one
asking the questions here.

15:48.240 --> 15:51.676
Okay. I like foreign movies,
old movies,

15:51.710 --> 15:53.575
like Truffaut and Godard.

15:54.680 --> 15:55.612
Tramp-boarding.

15:56.750 --> 15:58.581
Um...

15:58.620 --> 16:00.451
wh-what's that?

16:00.490 --> 16:02.549
Skateboarding on
a trampoline,

16:02.590 --> 16:04.023
without wheels.

16:04.060 --> 16:06.381
I know.
(laughs)

16:06.430 --> 16:09.251
But I can do a double somersault
from a full-blown ollie.

16:09.300 --> 16:10.699
To be honest,

16:10.730 --> 16:13.699
I've had an offer
from Canning & Meyers.

16:13.740 --> 16:16.493
But I really do
want to work here.

16:16.540 --> 16:19.566
I like the family spirit.
Well, if you
could hold off

16:19.610 --> 16:22.579
Canning & Meyers, we can
get back to you in a few days.

16:22.610 --> 16:24.544
That's great.
