Yes, he's ordered
the deaths

27:41.090 --> 27:42.819
of four witnesses
from prison.

27:42.860 --> 27:45.124
You want me to testify
against him?

27:45.160 --> 27:46.081
No. The deal's not
for what you know.

27:46.130 --> 27:47.791
It's for what
you'll find out.

27:47.830 --> 27:49.718
CARY:
We don't think you're
the most trustworthy witness.

27:49.760 --> 27:52.194
That's why we'll need you
to wear a wire.

27:52.230 --> 27:54.369
CELESTE:
That wasn't the deal.

27:54.400 --> 27:55.958
Well, that's the new deal.

27:56.000 --> 27:59.128
We're arranging to have Pike
transferred to another prison,

27:59.170 --> 28:00.774
they'll route him
through County.

28:00.810 --> 28:02.209
Mr. Sweeney and Pike

28:02.240 --> 28:04.800
will have three hours
together in the yard.

28:04.850 --> 28:07.045
Get him to admit to his newest
murder, and you're free.

28:07.080 --> 28:08.377
No. It's too dangerous.

28:08.420 --> 28:11.719
CARY:
Is it, Mr. Sweeney?

28:11.750 --> 28:12.887
Is it too dangerous?

28:14.260 --> 28:15.909
You don't want to do this.

28:15.960 --> 28:17.985
Alicia, it's his decision.

28:23.430 --> 28:25.421
You're gonna have
to supervise the wire.

28:26.870 --> 28:28.997
He thinks you care about him.

28:29.040 --> 28:31.907
What's even weirde_r--
you do care about him.

28:31.940 --> 28:33.874
No. I don't want him
getting killed.

28:33.910 --> 28:35.434
That's a pretty low bar
for caring.

28:35.480 --> 28:37.971
It's a pretty high bar
for a wife-killer.

28:38.010 --> 28:41.070
You're very
interesting, Alicia.

28:41.120 --> 28:42.769
How did you end up with Will?

28:44.490 --> 28:46.742
What makes you think
we ended up together?

28:46.790 --> 28:48.212
Will's attitude.

28:48.260 --> 28:49.409
He's smitten.

28:49.460 --> 28:51.382
Really? Smitten.

28:51.430 --> 28:53.250
Feels like the right word.

28:53.290 --> 28:55.258
It's sweet

28:55.300 --> 28:58.827
and high school, and

28:58.870 --> 28:59.996
very vanilla.

29:00.030 --> 29:01.167
That's no slam on you.

29:01.200 --> 29:02.758
(laughing)

29:02.800 --> 29:04.358
No, of course not.

29:04.410 --> 29:05.866
But what about you?

29:05.910 --> 29:07.263
You broke up with Will

29:07.310 --> 29:08.538
nine years ago?

29:08.580 --> 29:11.174
And yet, here you are,
trying to hurt him.

29:11.210 --> 29:12.199
Talk about high school.

29:12.250 --> 29:13.399
(laughs)

29:13.450 --> 29:15.008
(door opens)

29:15.050 --> 29:17.348
What do you think
you're doing?!
David.

29:17.380 --> 29:19.314
She's my niece.
I told you she's my niece.

29:19.350 --> 29:22.217
Oh, wait a minute. You-You
told me to hire who I wanted.

29:22.260 --> 29:24.228
Yes, and I told you
she was my niece.

29:24.260 --> 29:25.784
What else do you need to know?

29:25.830 --> 29:27.229
Look, David, Caitlin's good.

29:27.260 --> 29:29.524
She's very good,
and she'll find another job.

29:29.560 --> 29:30.891
This isn't about another.

29:30.930 --> 29:33.262
Don't you dare cross me again.

29:33.300 --> 29:34.164
You said
you didn't want nepotism.

29:34.200 --> 29:35.565
quwm

29:35.600 --> 29:37.261
there was no nepotism.

29:37.300 --> 29:39.530
You are a third-year associate.

29:39.570 --> 29:41.276
You were given this task

29:41.310 --> 29:43.870
because you are unimportant,
and you can take a hint.

29:43.910 --> 29:45.798
So take the hint,

29:45.850 --> 29:48.819
or we'll take it out
of your hands.

29:50.990 --> 29:52.241
(door closes)

29:57.190 --> 29:59.420
Let's get a drink.

29:59.460 --> 30:01.155
Mmm.

30:01.200 --> 30:03.498
You know the
best revenge?

30:03.530 --> 30:05.066
Hide his Bluetooth.

30:05.100 --> 30:06.192
No. Hire his niece,

30:06.230 --> 30:08.130
and then make her life hell.

30:08.170 --> 30:10.161
Oh, my God, you are so right.

30:10.200 --> 30:12.168
You'll never do it.
No, I will do it.

30:12.210 --> 30:13.939
I'm not a good person.

30:13.980 --> 30:15.277
Yes, you are.

30:15.310 --> 30:17.335
Shut up.

30:17.380 --> 30:18.472
I just don't like women.

30:18.510 --> 30:20.171
I find them uninteresting.

30:22.250 --> 30:24.218
Excuse me?

30:24.250 --> 30:25.842
I don't like women.

30:25.890 --> 30:27.243
They're all competing with me.

30:27.290 --> 30:28.359
Don't men compete with you?

30:28.390 --> 30:30.255
No, they don't.

30:30.290 --> 30:32.053
You have
female friends?

30:32.090 --> 30:33.557
No,

30:33.590 --> 30:35.899
but I don't have
any male friends, either.

30:35.930 --> 30:37.557
(laughs)

30:37.600 --> 30:39.898
That's so sad.

30:39.930 --> 30:42.034
I'd be your friend,
but I can't.

30:42.070 --> 30:43.037
Why not?

30:43.070 --> 30:44.332
Because. Will.

30:44.370 --> 30:46.235
Ah, that's right.

30:46.270 --> 30:48.204
Yeah.

30:48.240 --> 30:50.037
I don't like you
being with him.

30:50.080 --> 30:52.048
I'm gonna break you two up.

30:53.550 --> 30:55.518
Okay. How?

30:55.550 --> 30:57.848
How will I do it?

30:59.020 --> 31:02.012
I will... tell you about him.

31:02.060 --> 31:04.028
Well, go ahead.

31:04.060 --> 31:06.085
Give me your worst.

31:07.290 --> 31:09.258
No. I like you.

31:09.300 --> 31:10.528
See, that's your problem.

31:10.560 --> 31:12.221
You built it up too much,

31:12.270 --> 31:15.262
so if he hasn't buried
a hobo in the desert,

31:15.300 --> 31:17.291
I will be unimpressed.

31:17.340 --> 31:19.160
Oh, that's ancient history
anyway.

31:19.210 --> 31:21.235
And it was only $45,000.

31:21.280 --> 31:22.429
That's all?

31:22.480 --> 31:24.175
Yup, and he put it back.

31:24.210 --> 31:25.677
(laughs)

31:25.710 --> 31:27.917
You're so bad at this.

31:27.950 --> 31:29.679
(laughs)

31:29.720 --> 31:32.086
Yeah, I know. I'm sorry.

31:32.120 --> 31:35.157
I'm transparent as cellophane.

31:39.390 --> 31:41.358
I got to go.

31:41.400 --> 31:42.389
You're kidding.
Nope.

31:42.430 --> 31:47.367
Just remember, Will is like me.

31:47.400 --> 31:49.436
He'll always disappoint you.

31:49.470 --> 31:52.462
*

32:03.550 --> 32:05.347
(buzzing, indistinct chatter)

32:05.390 --> 32:07.381
MAN (over P.A.):
Attention, attention...

32:07.420 --> 32:11.220
(announcement continues
indistinctly)

32:11.260 --> 32:13.581
TECH:
The microphone is sewn
into your collar, Mr. Sweeney.

32:13.630 --> 32:14.699
Just keep your hands
away from it.

32:14.730 --> 32:16.721
Mm-hmm, very clever.

32:16.760 --> 32:18.421
Testing, testing!

32:18.470 --> 32:20.688
Just a normal voice,
Mr. Sweeney.

32:22.270 --> 32:25.239
Okay, so just
to remind you,

32:25.270 --> 32:28.000
Pike you know,

32:28.040 --> 32:30.235
but this fine citizen here
is Darryl Boyd,

32:30.280 --> 32:32.043
Pike's lieutenant
on the outside.

32:32.080 --> 32:34.674
Pike orders a hit in here, Boyd
carries it out on the street.

32:34.720 --> 32:37.712
This is Garfield Park
just last week.

32:37.750 --> 32:42.050
CARY:
You get Pike to admit he
ordered the Garfield Park hit,

32:42.090 --> 32:43.489
and I sign your
release authorization.

32:43.520 --> 32:45.488
Simple as that, huh?

32:45.530 --> 32:47.589
I'll be right here,
Mr. Sweeney, watching.

32:47.630 --> 32:49.450
Anything goes wrong,

32:49.500 --> 32:50.296
just walk away.

32:50.330 --> 32:52.389
They have security guards
standing by.

32:52.430 --> 32:55.137
They won't get there in time.

32:55.170 --> 32:59.266
When things happen, Mrs.
Florrick, they happen fast.

32:59.310 --> 33:02.336
Well, don't get
yourself killed, okay?

33:02.380 --> 33:05.474
Words to live by.

33:05.510 --> 33:07.307
CARY:
Okay,

33:07.350 --> 33:09.079
here we go.
Break a leg.

33:19.690 --> 33:22.124
(indistinct chatter)

33:22.160 --> 33:23.127
Hey, it's Sweeney.

33:23.160 --> 33:24.161
What's up, paperboy?

33:25.130 --> 33:27.223
It's all right, he's cool.

33:27.270 --> 33:28.635
Donald, hey.

33:28.670 --> 33:30.638
PIKE: _
What are you domg here?

33:30.670 --> 33:31.637
SWEENEY:
Testifying.

33:31.670 --> 33:33.399
Some civil case.

33:33.440 --> 33:36.170
Just an excuse
for a vacation, actually.

33:36.210 --> 33:38.098
I talked it up
so they'd go for it.

33:38.150 --> 33:39.708
PIKE:
So what's going on
with the market?

33:39.750 --> 33:41.513
Did you see HP?

33:41.550 --> 33:43.541
SWEENEY:
Yeah, don't worry.

33:43.580 --> 33:47.516
Sell at 20
and you'll be fine.

33:47.550 --> 33:51.088
Listen, Donald, I wanted
to ask you about something.

33:51.130 --> 33:55.499
Um, I read about Garfield Park
in the paper.

33:55.530 --> 33:58.419
Was that you?

33:58.470 --> 33:59.823
What is he doing?

33:59.870 --> 34:01.269
PIKE:
Why you talking about stuff

34:01.300 --> 34:03.131
that don't concern you, Sweeney?

34:03.170 --> 34:04.467
No, no, no,
I was just wondering.

34:04.510 --> 34:05.465
Well, don't.

34:05.510 --> 34:07.603
You know, you're funny.

34:07.640 --> 34:11.098
Like a pet.

34:11.150 --> 34:13.277
Don't make me
put you down.

34:18.890 --> 34:21.586
I like him.

34:21.620 --> 34:22.712
ELI:
I like him, too.

34:22.760 --> 34:23.556
He has a good story.

34:23.590 --> 34:26.286
He does-- prison,
wrongful conviction,

34:26.330 --> 34:28.389
back from the dead.

34:28.430 --> 34:29.419
He'd make a good keynote.

34:29.460 --> 34:30.427
He speaks well.

34:30.460 --> 34:31.791
He does.

34:31.830 --> 34:34.298
So?

34:34.340 --> 34:37.798
I just don't want him
to blow up in our face.

34:37.840 --> 34:40.468
How would he blow up
in your face?

34:40.510 --> 34:42.068
His marriage.

34:43.540 --> 34:45.508
Are you hearing
something?

34:45.550 --> 34:46.505
Of course I am.

34:46.550 --> 34:48.313
I'm hearing
they live apart,

34:48.350 --> 34:50.545
and if I'm
hearing it,

34:50.580 --> 34:52.582
the Republicans are
hearing it, too.

34:52.620 --> 34:54.258
If they were hearing it,
they'd use it.

34:54.290 --> 34:56.155
No, they would do
what we would do--

34:56.190 --> 34:58.488
release it the day
before he speaks.

35:00.690 --> 35:03.488
Of course you don't have
an issue with it, Eli.

35:03.530 --> 35:05.259
Peter Flo_rrick
is in office.

35:05.300 --> 35:07.518
When he runs for governor,
they will use it.

35:07.570 --> 35:11.336
They will use all of it, not
just on him but his wife, too.

35:14.510 --> 35:17.434
What if I promised
they'd be together?

35:18.780 --> 35:20.748
Is that a promise you can keep?

35:20.780 --> 35:22.247
Yes, it is.

35:22.280 --> 35:25.613
Then we'll consider
him for keynote.

35:25.650 --> 35:28.153
Again, Eli,
I like him.

35:28.190 --> 35:30.488
He's a thoroughbred,

35:30.520 --> 35:34.729
but I just can't
risk... risk.

35:41.970 --> 35:44.359
Okay, here he goes.
IMANI:
We've got about ten
minutes before they return

35:44.410 --> 35:45.160
to their cells.

35:45.210 --> 35:46.837
I thought we were
done talking.

35:46.870 --> 35:49.600
I-I-I want to know
about Garfield Park.

35:49.640 --> 35:51.471
Is he out of his mind?

35:51.510 --> 35:52.499
MAN:
Look at this guy.

35:52.550 --> 35:53.505
What are you, stupid?

35:53.550 --> 35:54.414
What, are you
smoking crack

35:54.450 --> 35:56.645
with the brothers?
Get the guard ready.

35:56.680 --> 35:57.942
I think he looks like a snitch.

35:57.980 --> 35:59.789
Think he looks like a snitch?
Go now, Cary.

35:59.820 --> 36:02.653
He's a snitch.

36:02.690 --> 36:03.679
You got to pull him out now.

36:03.720 --> 36:05.449
We pull him out now, no deal.

36:05.490 --> 36:06.525
Wait, listen.

36:06.560 --> 36:10.189
Hey, hey, Donald,
H didn't mean anything by it.

36:10.230 --> 36:11.697
Why the hell do
you keep asking?

36:11.730 --> 36:13.368
'Cause I-I need
your help.

36:13.400 --> 36:14.765
You know what they did.

36:14.800 --> 36:16.688
They took my company from me.

36:16.740 --> 36:19.265
PIKE:
Everybody here's got
a story, paperboy.

36:19.310 --> 36:20.732
What makes you so special?

36:20.770 --> 36:22.533
SWEENEY:
I have money...

36:22.580 --> 36:25.674
and I want the man
who did this dead.

36:25.710 --> 36:27.769
Gerald Drescher.

36:27.810 --> 36:29.414
He used to be my vice president

36:29.450 --> 36:33.409
until he stabbed me
in the back.

36:33.450 --> 36:34.883
You're serious?

36:34.920 --> 36:37.252
How much
would it cost?

36:37.290 --> 36:39.554
PIKE:
A guy like that has security.

36:43.900 --> 36:45.265
Uh,

36:45.300 --> 36:48.565
job like that--
it'll cost a lot of money.

36:48.600 --> 36:51.865
That's why I got to know
what I'm getting.

36:51.910 --> 36:53.730
Okay, here he goes, nice move.

36:53.770 --> 36:54.771
You're pushing
it, Sweeney.

36:54.810 --> 36:57.677
You're in prison.

36:57.710 --> 37:00.270
I'm asking,
how can you get it done?

37:08.720 --> 37:10.756
All right, sure.

37:11.960 --> 37:15.657
Garfield Park--
yeah, that was me.

37:15.700 --> 37:19.989
My boy on the outside--
I get word to through my sister.

37:21.030 --> 37:25.000
I give the green light,
he does the hit.

37:25.040 --> 37:27.406
(sighs)

37:27.440 --> 37:29.533
A hit on his vice president,
huh?

37:29.580 --> 37:32.003
Oh, come on,
he had to say something.

37:32.050 --> 37:33.574
You have _ _
the release authorization?

37:33.610 --> 37:36.773
Already blessed by Judge Romano.

37:37.780 --> 37:39.919
(chuckles)

37:39.950 --> 37:41.918
Pleasure doing
business with you.

37:50.860 --> 37:52.896
DIANE:
Is your health issue from the
other day better, Mr. Sweeney?

37:52.930 --> 37:55.034
Much better, thank you.

37:55.070 --> 37:57.698
My goodness, I must
have made a fuss here.

37:57.740 --> 37:59.628
Food poisoning.

37:59.670 --> 38:01.638
Uh, now, Mr. Sweeney,
you testified

38:01.680 --> 38:04.672
that you were present
at the IPO meeting?

38:04.710 --> 38:06.507
That's right.

38:06.550 --> 38:08.370
DIANE:
And did you hear
any discussion

38:08.420 --> 38:09.910
about the deicing in the wings?

38:09.950 --> 38:11.645
SWEENEY:
Oh, yes,

38:11.690 --> 38:16.855
I heard everything,
and it's not good.

38:22.760 --> 38:26.821
Good job, I, I hear you saved
some kind of case today.

38:26.870 --> 38:29.395
Oh, I just-- we
got a settlement.

38:29.440 --> 38:31.738
Great, great.

38:31.770 --> 38:33.032
We should talk sometime.

38:33.070 --> 38:34.537
About?

38:34.580 --> 38:35.774
The future.
(chuckles)

38:35.810 --> 38:37.004
What else?

38:42.450 --> 38:44.418
I'm so sorry I'm late.

38:44.450 --> 38:46.589
Thank you for coming
back in, Martha.

38:46.620 --> 38:49.817
I just had a few more
questions before we decide.

38:49.860 --> 38:51.589
Before you...?

38:51.630 --> 38:52.722
What are you talking about?

38:52.760 --> 38:53.852
They already decided.

38:53.890 --> 38:55.755
I-I'm sorry, what?

38:55.800 --> 38:57.552
I didn't get
the job here.

38:57.600 --> 38:59.488
I turned down my other job

38:59.530 --> 39:01.498
because I thought I had
this, and now...

39:01.540 --> 39:03.735
I can't believe this.

39:03.770 --> 39:05.863
Well, who told you
you didn't get this?
The hiring committee.

39:05.910 --> 39:06.763
They called.

39:06.810 --> 39:08.937
Well, there must be
some sort of mistake,

39:08.980 --> 39:10.777
because I haven't decided yet.

39:10.810 --> 39:12.402
No, they did.

39:12.450 --> 39:15.078
He said I was close,
but they had a vote.

39:15.120 --> 39:16.940
So what happened?

39:18.490 --> 39:20.048
(elevator bell dings)

39:20.090 --> 39:22.058
Now, your office is
on the 27th floor,

39:22.090 --> 39:24.684
but I want to show you
around here first.

39:24.730 --> 39:25.719
Now, this...
Alicia!

39:25.760 --> 39:27.819
Thank you so much.

39:27.860 --> 39:29.589
I am just so thrilled.

39:29.630 --> 39:31.052
David said it was all you.

39:31.100 --> 39:33.762
You picked me,
and you're gonna
be my mentor.

39:33.800 --> 39:35.995
Yes, Alicia, thank you.

39:37.470 --> 39:39.961
You're welcome.
Anyway, I
am really

39:40.010 --> 39:41.898
looking forward to
working with you.

39:41.940 --> 39:43.931
Thank you again.

39:53.790 --> 39:56.953
I don't get it. Why put me
through the charade...

39:56.990 --> 39:59.424
Alicia..
No. I want to know.

39:59.460 --> 40:00.927
I never had any power, did I?

40:00.960 --> 40:02.120
It was all rigged.

40:03.860 --> 40:05.566
David Lee appealed
to the hiring committee,

40:05.600 --> 40:07.568
and the hiring committee
voted to go another way.

40:07.600 --> 40:08.965
That's all.
It happens.

40:15.710 --> 40:17.678
Which way did you vote?

40:17.710 --> 40:19.007
On what?

40:19.050 --> 40:20.938
The committee voted for Caitlin
and against Martha.

40:20.980 --> 40:22.470
Which way did you vote?

40:24.820 --> 40:27.118
I voted with David Lee.

40:29.120 --> 40:30.815
Why?

40:32.760 --> 40:34.648
Because I owed him.

40:34.700 --> 40:35.792
For what?

40:35.830 --> 40:37.798
You don't want to know.
I do want to know.

40:37.830 --> 40:39.058
I feel used, Will.

40:39.100 --> 40:43.662
I feel like I was given a job
and it was taken away from me.

40:49.210 --> 40:51.701
(clicks pen closed)

40:51.750 --> 40:54.844
There was a Martha
when we hired you, Alicia.

40:55.880 --> 40:57.040
On paper,

40:57.080 --> 41:01.016
she was the better candidate
and you were the... Caitlin.

41:06.090 --> 41:08.752
You were gonna lose in a vote.

41:08.800 --> 41:12.224
I asked David Lee
to vote with me.

41:14.030 --> 41:16.134
So I owed him.

41:22.040 --> 41:23.678
You okay?

41:30.080 --> 41:32.878
Thank you.

41:32.920 --> 41:34.979
Caitlins often surprise you.

